article.headline: E. Michigan 61, Manhattan 57
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Sophomore forward Justin Dobbins had a career-high 22 points and 14 rebounds, Jesse Bunkley added 19 points and Eastern Michigan overcame a 13-point second-half deficit to defeat Manhattan 61-57 on Wednesday night. Bunkley, scoreless in the first half, equaled his career high for 3-point field goals by hitting 6-of-7 from behind the arc after intermission for the visiting Eagles (2-2). Antoine Pearson scored 15 points and Devon Austin has 13 for the Jaspers (2-2). Patrick Bouli had all nine of his points in the first half to help Manhattan take a 27-17 halftime lead. Jarred Axon's 3-pointer with 12:25 left in the game capped an 18-5 Eastern Michigan scoring run that tied the game at 35. The teams traded 3-pointers and the lead changed hands seven times after that, with the Jaspers last leading 50-49 after Austin's trey with 4:55 to go. The Eagles went ahead to stay at 52-50 on Bunkley's 3-pointer with 4:19 remaining.
